The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and cuts, which are typical topics in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the L Bounded Cut problem, which is a graph theoretic problem. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and complexity results, which are typical topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
